---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Work & Background | Sam Onishi"
  description="Project experience across music, digital platforms, events, environmental initiatives, and corporate production—1995–2009 and beyond."
  wide
>
  <article class="page-content work-page">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Work &amp; Background</h1>
      <p class="lead">Supporting and coordinating roles across cultural, creative, nonprofit, and corporate contexts.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="work-body">
      <div class="work-intro-block">
        <div class="prose intro">
          <p>
            Between 1995 and 2009, Sam was engaged in a wide range of independent, cross-border
            projects across cultural, creative, nonprofit, and corporate contexts.
          </p>
          <p>
            During this period, he primarily worked in supporting and coordinating roles, helping bridge
            organizations, teams, and individuals operating across different countries, languages, and
            institutional environments. His work consistently emphasized communication support, operational
            coordination, and practical execution rather than public-facing leadership or advocacy.
          </p>
        </div>
        <figure class="work-visual">
          <img src="/organizer.png" alt="Collaborative work: cross-border operations and multilingual localization" width="800" height="533" />
          <figcaption>Cross-border operations &amp; multilingual coordination</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <h2 class="section-title">Project Themes</h2>
      <div class="project-grid">
      <section class="project-card">
        <h3>Music &amp; Entertainment Project Support</h3>
        <p>
          Sam supported early-stage music and entertainment initiatives, assisting with group formation,
          coordination among creative teams, and operational support in live performance settings.
          His role often involved working behind the scenes to help align expectations and workflows
          between organizations and individuals from different cultural and organizational backgrounds.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-card">
        <h3>Digital &amp; Platform Support for International Organizations</h3>
        <p>
          He contributed to the setup and management of websites and online platforms for international
          and nonprofit organizations, supporting multilingual content organization and cross-border communication.
          This work included assisting with information structure, localization, and internal coordination to
          help organizations operate more effectively across regions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-card">
        <h3>Events, Festivals &amp; Live Production Support</h3>
        <p>
          Sam assisted in the production and coordination of large-scale cultural events, including festivals,
          pageant-related projects, and international live productions. His involvement focused on logistics
          support, documentation, backstage operations, and coordination between production teams working
          in different countries and institutional settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-card">
        <h3>Environmental &amp; Community-Based Project Support</h3>
        <p>
          He also supported cross-border environmental and humanitarian initiatives, coordinating projects
          that connected Japanese nonprofit organizations with local public-sector and civil-society
          stakeholders in Southeast Asia. These activities included support for reforestation efforts and
          disaster-relief-related initiatives, with Sam focusing on communication support, organizational
          coordination, and practical assistance at the project level.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-card">
        <h3>Corporate &amp; Advertising Production Support</h3>
        <p>
          Sam supported advertising and production-related projects involving Japanese corporations
          operating overseas. He assisted production teams working on local advertising initiatives in
          Southeast Asia, supporting coordination between Japanese corporate stakeholders and local
          creative and operational teams—centering on communication support, on-site coordination,
          and bridging differences in working styles and expectations.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

      <div class="prose closing">
      <p>
        Across these projects, Sam consistently worked in roles that required navigating complexity
        between organizations from different countries and sectors. This period shaped his approach
        to organizational operations and co-founder-style support in later years, emphasizing
        structure, execution, and continuity over visibility or personal attribution.
      </p>
      </div>

      <p class="note">
        For updated professional information, please refer to LinkedIn.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <style>
    .work-page {
      max-width: 52rem;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .page-header {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
      font-weight: 400;
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .page-header .lead {
      margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .work-body {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0;
    }

    .work-intro-block {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
      gap: 2rem 2.5rem;
      align-items: start;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    .prose {
      max-width: none;
    }

    .work-page .prose {
      min-width: 0;
    }

    .prose p {
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
    }

    .intro {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    .work-visual {
      margin: 0;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 320px;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      overflow: hidden;
      background: var(--line);
      box-shadow: 0 1px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
    }

    .work-visual img {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }

    .work-visual figcaption {
      padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      background: var(--surface);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .section-title {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--muted);
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
      padding-top: 0.25rem;
    }

    .project-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 1.25rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .project-card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 1.35rem;
      min-height: 0;
    }

    .project-card h3 {
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.35;
    }

    .project-card p {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .closing {
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      max-width: 60ch;
    }

    .closing p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    .note {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--muted-light);
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .work-intro-block {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }

      .work-visual {
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .project-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
